                  <additions>
                     <p><locus>Folio 1r</locus> contains the following Mughal inscriptions: Transfer
                        from <persName role="oth" key="person_f8364">Muʻnim Bayg</persName> to <persName
                           role="oth" key="person_f8365">Murād Bayg</persName>, certified by <persName
                              role="oth" key="person_f8366">Muḥammad Rashīd</persName>, inspector
                           (<term>mushrif</term>), dated 29 Zu’l-Ḥijjah year 50 (1117, 13 April
                        1706); transfer from Murād Bayg to <persName role="oth" key="person_f8367">ʻAẓīm
                           Bayg</persName>, dated 7 Rajab year 2 (1120, 22 Sept 1708); transfer from
                        ʻAẓīm Bayg to … [illegible] Bayg, dated 3 Rabīʻ I year 3 (1121, 13 May
                        1709), and a valuation of Rs. 18(?); and an inspection dated 19 Rabīʻ I(?)
                        year 3 (1121, 29 May 1709). </p>
                     <p>Wrapper made of re-used list of works in the Delhi Persian collection. </p>
                  </additions>
