               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="1678" notAfter="1683">Copied between
                        1678 (date of composition) and 1683 (death of librarian Sayyid ʻAlī
                        al-Husayni)</origDate>
                     <origPlace>India</origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Entered the Mughal imperial library during the lifetime of the librarian
                        Sayyid ʻAlī al-Ḥusayni (d. 1683) (his damaged seal, most likely dated RY 8,
                        1075/1665); remained there at least until 1709 (inscriptions dated regnal
                        year 3 most likely of Bahadur Shah ʻAlam (r. 1707-12). </p>
                     <p>Acquired by unknown owners (indecipherable rectangular seals, f.1v and
                        octagonal seal, f.1r). </p>
                     <p>Purchased by the Government of India at sale organised by Delhi Prize
                        Agents, 1859; administrative deposit India Office Library, 1876. </p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Acquired by the Government of India in <date>1876</date></p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
